transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hey, John. My name is Morris Wright, W-R-I-G-H-T.

Speaker 1: I'm on a replenishment program with Square Blue.

Speaker 2: The problem is I asked for the A-G-V, I believe it's called, and I'm not getting that.

Speaker 1: I have two orders that I've gotten from you off the floor, and it's just regular cylinder fill.

Speaker 2: Well, let me get that fixed for you, sir. What's your zip code?

Speaker 1: 1-9-4-0-1.

Speaker 2: One second, please.

Speaker 1: Are you at 560 Stambridge in Norristown?

Speaker 2: That is correct.

Speaker 1: I know what it says on the label, and I believe you, but do you have any of the pills with you currently?

Speaker 2: I've got them right in my hand.

Speaker 1: Do you just mind humoring me and telling me what's stamped on an actual pill?

Speaker 2: One second.

Speaker 1: Let me just put a light on this for a minute so I'm telling you the right thing.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: I'm not as sure.

Speaker 2: It has some initials on there, A-C-3-4-

Speaker 1: No, and it says A-C tells me enough.

Speaker 2: So you did get the wrong thing, sir.

Speaker 1: So I'm going to fix this for you.

Speaker 2: I'm going to send you out 20 pills, because that's what you're owed, obviously,

Speaker 1: and then as a courtesy to you just for the hassle, I can actually take some off your price here for future orders, too.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Say that again, please, John, because you confuse me.

Speaker 2: You're saying that I've gotten two orders so far from you are the wrong thing.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So now you're going to send me out 20 pills.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry?

Speaker 1: I'm replacing both for free, so you're going to get 20 pills.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: This was 20?

Speaker 2: No, you got 10 each time.

Speaker 1: You've had two orders that were wrong, so I need to replace both orders.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'm replacing your first and your second order,

Speaker 2: and then I was saying just as a token of, like, goodwill because of the inconvenience here,

Speaker 1: I have the authority I can knock your price down a little bit on future orders,

Speaker 2: so I'm just going to give you a break there, too.

Speaker 1: I appreciate that, John.

Speaker 2: You're welcome, Morris.

Speaker 1: So I'll get this taken care of on my side, okay?

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Of course.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: You, too.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
